greetings my name is Matt Wood and I'm
here at the AWS headquarters in Seattle
to give you an update on the Amazon
simple Q service sqs sqs is a fully
managed message queuing service for
reliably communicating between
distributed software components and
microservices at any scale sqs makes it
simple to decouple application
components so they can run and fail
independently this lets you build
applications that are def fault tolerant
and easy to scale with sqs you can
exchange messages between any number of
systems at any volume without losing
messages and without the overhead of
managing dedicated messaging software
and
infrastructure now sqs gives you even
more power and flexibility with the
introduction of an entirely New Q type
called fifo or first in first out fifo
cues are designed to guarantee that the
order in which messages are placed on a
queue is the order in which they will be
retrieved from it this lets you use sqs
for systems that depend on receiving
messages in exact order and exactly once
such as financial services and
e-commerce
applications for example fqs help ensure
Mobile Banking transactions are
processed in the correct sequence and
that price updates for online retail
sites like Amazon are processed and
published in the right order fifo qes
complement our existing sqs standard
cues which offer higher throughput best
effort ordering and at least once
delivery the same API functions apply to
both types of Q's Amazon sqs 5o Q's are
priced at 50 cents per million API
requests with the first 1 million
monthly requests free today we have
expanded sqs 5qs to us East Virginia
region you can get started with sqs 5qs
using the AWS console or SDK of your
choice with just three simple commands
that's it thanks a lot
